On Strapi, you can use **objects** to make deep filters (https://docs.strapi.io/developer-docs/latest/developer-resources/database-apis-reference/rest/filtering-locale-publication.html#deep-filtering)
Example:
```
filters: {
    chef: {
      restaurants: {
        stars: {
          $eq: 5,
        },
      },
    },
},
```
GET /api/restaurants?filters[chef][restaurants][stars][$eq]=5

Refine, only allows **arrays**, with logical filters or conditional filters  (https://refine.dev/docs/guides-and-concepts/data-provider/handling-filters/):
Example:
```
const filter = [
    {
        field: "name",
        operator: "eq",
        value: "John",
    },
